headline: BlackRock Caps 2025 With Record $14 Trillion in Assets
summary: BlackRock’s  assets topped $14 trillion for the first time, while the money manager’s quarterly profit fell on one-time costs stemming from a recent acquisition spree.  BlackRock posted net income of $1.13 billion, down 33% from a year earlier.  Base fees, or investment management fees that aren’t related to fund performance, grew 9% from a year earlier when stripping out the impact of market moves.

headline: BlackRock’s Profit Fell, Assets Hit Record $14 Trillion, in Fourth Quarter
summary: BlackRock’s  profit fell in the fourth quarter on higher expenses, and the world’s largest money manager ended 2025 with more than $14 trillion in assets for the first time.  BlackRock posted net income of $1.13 billion, down 33% from a year earlier.  The stock market rebounded sharply from April, when fears about the effects of President Trump’s tariff plans sent the major indexes reeling, and ended 2025 near record highs.

headline: BlackRock Assets Hit Record $14 Trillion
summary: BlackRock reported fourth-quarter net income of $1.13 billion, down 33% from the prior year, while assets under management rose 22% to a record $14 trillion. On a per-share basis, net income was $7.16, falling short of analysts’ forecast for $11.
